{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd43-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"817"},"text":"§ 817.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Treatment of variable contracts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd44-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Increases and decreases in reserves","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of subsections (a) and (b) of section 807, the sum of the items described in section 807(c) taken into account as of the close of the taxable year with respect to any variable contract shall, under regulations prescribed by the Secretary, be adjusted—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd45-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" by subtracting therefrom an amount equal to the sum of the amounts added from time to time (for the taxable year) to the reserves separately accounted for in accordance with subsection (c) by reason of appreciation in value of assets (whether or not the assets have been disposed of), and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd46-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" by adding thereto an amount equal to the sum of the amounts subtracted from time to time (for the taxable year) from such reserves by reason of depreciation in value of assets (whether or not the assets have been disposed of).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"The deduction allowable for items described in paragraphs (1) and (6) of section 805(a) with respect to variable contracts shall be reduced to the extent that the amount of such items is increased for the taxable year by appreciation (or increased to the extent that the amount of such items is decreased for the taxable year by depreciation) not reflected in adjustments under the preceding sentence.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd47-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Adjustment to basis of assets held in segregated asset account","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of variable contracts, the basis of each asset in a segregated asset account shall (in addition to all other adjustments to basis) be—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd48-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" increased by the amount of any appreciation in value, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd49-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" decreased by the amount of any depreciation in value,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"to the extent such appreciation and depreciation are from time to time reflected in the increases and decreases in reserves or other items referred to in subsection (a) with respect to such contracts.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd4a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Separate accounting","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this part, a life insurance company which issues variable contracts shall separately account for the various income, exclusion, deduction, asset, reserve, and other liability items properly attributable to such variable contracts. For such items as are not accounted for directly, separate accounting shall be made—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd4b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in accordance with the method regularly employed by such company, if such method is reasonable, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd4c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in all other cases, in accordance with regulations prescribed by the Secretary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd4d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Variable contract defined","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this part, the term “variable contract” means a contract—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd4e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" which provides for the allocation of all or part of the amounts received under the contract to an account which, pursuant to State law or regulation, is segregated from the general asset accounts of the company,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd4f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" which—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd50-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provides for the payment of annuities,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd51-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is a life insurance contract, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd52-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provides for funding of insurance on retired lives as described in section 807(c)(6), and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd53-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" under which—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd54-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of an annuity contract, the amounts paid in, or the amount paid out, reflect the investment return and the market value of the segregated asset account,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd55-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of a life insurance contract, the amount of the death benefit (or the period of coverage) is adjusted on the basis of the investment return and the market value of the segregated asset account, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd56-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/d/3/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of funds held under a contract described in paragraph (2)(C), the amounts paid in, or the amounts paid out, reflect the investment return and the market value of the segregated asset account.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"If a contract ceases to reflect current investment return and current market value, such contract shall not be considered as meeting the requirements of paragraph (3) after such cessation. Paragraph (3) shall be applied without regard to whether there is a guarantee, and obligations under such guarantee which exceed obligations under the contract without regard to such guarantee shall be accounted for as part of the company’s general account.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd57-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Pension plan contracts treated as paying annuity","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A pension plan contract which is not a life, accident, or health, property, casualty, or liability insurance contract shall be treated as a contract which provides for the payments of annuities for purposes of subsection (d).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd58-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Other special rules","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd59-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/f/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Life insurance reserves","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of subsection (b)(1)(A) of section 816, the reflection of the investment return and the market value of the segregated asset account shall be considered an assumed rate of interest.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd5a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/f/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Additional separate computations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Under regulations prescribed by the Secretary, such additional separate computations shall be made, with respect to the items separately accounted for in accordance with subsection (c), as may be necessary to carry out the purposes of this section and this part.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd5b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Variable annuity contracts treated as annuity contracts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this part, the term “annuity contract” includes a contract which provides for the payment of a variable annuity computed on the basis of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd5c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/g/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" recognized mortality tables, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd5d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/g/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd5e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/g/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the investment experience of a segregated asset account, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd5f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/g/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the company-wide investment experience of the company.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"Paragraph (2)(B) shall not apply to any company which issues contracts which are not variable contracts.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd60-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Treatment of certain nondiversified contracts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd61-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of subchapter L, section 72 (relating to annuities), and section 7702(a) (relating to definition of life insurance contract), a variable contract (other than a pension plan contract) which is otherwise described in this section and which is based on a segregated asset account shall not be treated as an annuity, endowment, or life insurance contract for any period (and any subsequent period) for which the investments made by such account are not, in accordance with regulations prescribed by the Secretary, adequately diversified.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd62-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Safe harbor for diversification","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A segregated asset account shall be treated as meeting the requirements of paragraph (1) for any quarter of a taxable year if as of the close of such quarter—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd63-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" it meets the requirements of section 851(b)(3), and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd64-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" no more than 55 percent of the value of the total assets of the account are assets described in section 851(b)(3)(A)(i).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd65-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Special rule for investments in United States obligations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"To the extent that any segregated asset account with respect to a variable life insurance contract is invested in securities issued by the United States Treasury, the investments made by such account shall be treated as adequately diversified for purposes of paragraph (1).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd66-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Look-through in certain cases","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this subsection, if all of the beneficial interests in a regulated investment company or in a trust are held by 1 or more—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd67-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" insurance companies (or affiliated companies) in their general account or in segregated asset accounts, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd68-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" fund managers (or affiliated companies) in connection with the creation or management of the regulated investment company or trust,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"the diversification requirements of paragraph (1) shall be applied by taking into account the assets held by such regulated investment company or trust.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd69-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Independent investment advisors permitted","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in this subsection shall be construed as prohibiting the use of independent investment advisors.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd6a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s817/h/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Government securities funds","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In determining whether a segregated asset account is adequately diversified for purposes of paragraph (1), each United States Government agency or instrumentality shall be treated as a separate issuer.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id4410dd6b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/dA/tII/s211/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, div. A, title II, § 211(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/750"},"text":"98 Stat. 750","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/tXVIII/s1821/m"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, title XVIII, § 1821(m)","children":[],"tail":", (t)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2841"},"text":"100 Stat. 2841","children":[],"tail":", 2844; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647/tVI/s6080/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647, title VI, § 6080(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/3710"},"text":"102 Stat. 3710","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/188/tI/s1611/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–188, title I, § 1611(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-20"},"text":"Aug. 20, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1845"},"text":"110 Stat. 1845","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/34/tXII/s1271/b/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–34, title XII, § 1271(b)(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/1037"},"text":"111 Stat. 1037","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/218/tII/s205/b/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–218, title II, § 205(b)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-04-10"},"text":"Apr. 10, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/610"},"text":"118 Stat. 610","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id4410dd6c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id4410dd6d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id4410dd6e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 817, added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/69/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–69, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1959","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/73/132"},"text":"73 Stat. 132","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/tXIV/s1402/b/1/M"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, title XIV, § 1402(b)(1)(M)","children":[],"tail":", (2), title XIX, §§ 1901(a)(100), 1951(b)(11)(A), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-04"},"text":"Oct. 4, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/1732"},"text":"90 Stat. 1732","children":[],"tail":", 1781, 1839, related to rules regarding certain gains and losses, prior to the general revision of this part by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s211/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 211(a)","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Another prior section 817, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736/s817"},"text":"act Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736, § 817","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-03-13/ch83/s2"},"text":"Mar. 13, 1956, ch. 83, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70/46"},"text":"70 Stat. 46","children":[],"tail":", related to denial of double deductions, prior to the general revision of this part by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/69/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–69, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id4410dd6f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/218"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–218","children":[],"tail":", in introductory provisions, struck out “(other than section 809)” after “For purposes of this part”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsec. (h)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/34/s1271/b/8/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–34, § 1271(b)(8)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “851(b)(3)” for “851(b)(4)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h)(2)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/34/s1271/b/8/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–34, § 1271(b)(8)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “851(b)(3)(A)(i)” for “851(b)(4)(A)(i)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (d)(2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/188/s1611/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–188, § 1611(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(3)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/188/s1611/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–188, § 1611(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (h)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647","children":[],"tail":" added par. (6)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s1821/t/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 1821(t)(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted at end “Paragraph (3) shall be applied without regard to whether there is a guarantee, and obligations under such guarantee which exceed obligations under the contract without regard to such guarantee shall be accounted for as part of the company’s general account.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s1821/m/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 1821(m)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out last sentence which read as follows: “For purposes of this paragraph and paragraph (2), beneficial interests in a regulated investment company or in a trust shall not be treated as 1 investment if all of the beneficial interests in such company or trust are held by 1 or more segregated asset accounts of 1 or more insurance companies.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h)(3) to (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s1821/m/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 1821(m)(1)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (3) and (4), redesignated former par. (4) as (5), and struck out former par. (3) which read as follows: “In the case of a segregated asset account with respect to variable life insurance contracts, paragraph (1) shall not apply in the case of securities issued by the United States Treasury which are owned by a regulated investment company or by a trust all the beneficial interests in which are held by 1 or more segregated asset accounts of the company issuing the contract.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id4410dd70-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id4410dd71-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2004 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/218"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–218","children":[],"tail":" applicable to taxable years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 2004","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/218/s205/c"},"text":"section 205(c) of Pub. L. 108–218","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s807"},"text":"section 807 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id4410dd72-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1997 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/34/tXII/s1271/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–34, title XII, § 1271(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/1037"},"text":"111 Stat. 1037","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/105/34/tXII/s1271/c"},"text":"“The amendments made by this section [amending this section and sections 851 and 1092 of this title] shall apply to taxable years beginning after the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1997","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id4410dd73-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1996 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/188/tI/s1611/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–188, title I, § 1611(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-20"},"text":"Aug. 20, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1846"},"text":"110 Stat. 1846","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/104/188/tI/s1611/b"},"text":"“The amendments made by this section [amending this section] shall apply to taxable years beginning after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1995","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id4410dd74-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1988 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647/tVI/s6080/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647, title VI, § 6080(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"